HEADWORD: gulfweed
<hw>gulf"weed`</hw> <pr>(g⟦ucr⟧lf"w⟦emac⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A brown seaweed (<spn>Sargassum bacciferum</spn>) with
rounded bladders forming dense floating masses in tropical Atlantic
waters as in the Sargasso Sea.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> sargassum, sargasso, <spn>Sargassum
bacciferum</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
